listDescription: Recognizes contributions to the launch and initial impact of Base, the OP Stack L2 incubated by Coinbase and the first Superchain OP Chain. You can find my conflict disclosure here: https://gov.optimism.io/t/badgeholder-conflict-of-interest-disclosures/5569/49?u=jessepollak.
impactEvaluationDescription: My high level methodology for voting on this was to assign a fixed distribution of points that I believe should be allocated to Base ecosystem, then: (1) Identify projects that I could personally attest to impact on; (2) Group the projects into Gold, Silver, Bronze, Steel impact based on my personal knowledge, incorporating a number of factors, including where in the lifecycle of the project things are; (3) Give Gold = 8 points, Silver = 2 points, Bronze = 1 point, Steel = 0.5 point then distribute the % based on the number of points normalized. For the fixed distribution of points to the Base ecosystem, I've chosen 33% of the total = 10m OP. I chose this number because: (1) Base played a major role in legitimizing the OP Stack and Optimism over the last 6 months as the first non-OP Mainnet chain to launch; (2) Base has contributed nearly $1m in ETH revenue to Optimism since launch; (3) Base has attracted $500m+ of assets to the superchain, 63m transactions, and 2.5m transacting addresses (dashboard); (4) Almost all of these projects also contributed to other Superchain chains, so they deserve recognition for that as well. I am excited to see these projects continue to make a positive impact on Base and the entire Superchain.
